<DOC><DOCNO> ZF310-598-745 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 598 745.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 15 1991 n416 p56(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Small makers tout powerful, lightweight portables.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Nunoo, Mildred.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Some smaller vendors are offering powerful and lightweight laptopcomputers to compete with products from Compaq, Toshiba and IBM.andO;Poqet Computer recently introduced the Poqet PC ($1,450), its mostportable, IBM-standard, MS-DOS laptop computer.andP;  Features includea full 80-character x 25-line display and a 77-key keyboard.andP;  Itfits inside a purse, briefcase or jacket pocket.andP;  It runs up to100 hours on two standard AA-size batteries.andP;  Applications areavailable on 'credit-card-sized' disks called Poqet PC cards.andP;  RDIComputer has introduced a laptop computer called BriteLite($10,800), which weighs 13 pounds and runs on Sun Microsystems'IPC board (motherboard).andP;  Fora Inc's market entry is the NBS-386S($2,995), which weighs 6.4 pounds.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Poqet Computer Corp. (Products)RDI Computer Corp. (Products)Fora Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Poqet Computer Poqet PC (Portable computer) (Design andconstruction)RDI Computer Britelite (Portable computer) (Design andconstruction)Fora NBS-386S (Portable computer) (Design and construction).andO;Topic:     Laptop ComputersNotebook ComputersPortable Computers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>